{{Family law}}
'''Mavis Maclean''' (born 31 December 1943),<ref name=Congress>{{cite web |title= Maclean, Mavis |url= http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79043938.html |publisher= Library of Congress |accessdate= 11 July 2014 |quote= CIP t.p. (Mavis Maclean) data sheet (b. 12/31/43)}}</ref> [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]], [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]], [[FAcSS]] has carried out [[Sociology of law#Socio-Legal Studies|socio-legal research]] at Oxford since 1974, and in 2001 founded the Oxford Centre for Family Law and Policy (OXFLAP).<ref name=OXFLAP>{{cite web|url=https://www.spi.ox.ac.uk/people/profile/maclean.html|title=Department of Social Policy and Intervention > Research Associate Mavis Maclean |accessdate=9 October 2013}}</ref>

In 1993 she was elected President of the Research Committee for the Sociology of Law, [[International Sociological Association]], in 2000 a Trustee of the Law and Society Association. Maclean founded Oxford Centre for Family Law and Policy (OXFLAP) in 2001, she is also a [[Royal Society of Arts|Fellow of the Royal Society of Arts]] and the [[Economic and Social Research Council|ESRC Research College SHARe]].<ref name=OXFLAP/> In 2011 she was the inaugural recipient of the Socio-Legal Studies Association's Prize for Contributions to the Socio-Legal Community.<ref>http://www.slsa.ac.uk/index.php/prizes-grants-and-seminars/prizewinners#SLSA</ref>

